cs.LG, cs.GT, cs.DS, cs.IT, cs.CC 

The paper deals with learning problems and sample complexity bounds, which are typically studied in the machine learning (cs.LG) and theoretical computer science (cs.THE) communities. The focus on product distributions and the lack of reliance on complexity measures suggests a connection to information theory (cs.IT) and combinatorics (cs.DS). The specific applications to auctions, prophet inequalities, and Pandora's problem suggest a connection to game theory (cs.GT) and computational complexity (cs.CC).
